## 1. Context and Background

This project originated as an **MVP (Minimum Viable Product)** developed by a student member of the **HEI Tech Madagascar** club. Its potential caught the attention of the Student Council (Bureau des Étudiants — BDE), which subsequently took over its maintenance and development to evolve it into a student life-focused tool.

The project is now maintained and developed by a dedicated **HEI Tech Madagascar club team**.

> ⚠️ Although developed within this student association context, the project and its source code are technically and legally **independent** from any official or administrative infrastructure of the HEI institution.

---

## 2. Restrictions on Use and Contribution

Any **use, copying, modification, distribution, publication, or sale** of this source code, in whole or in part, is **strictly prohibited** for any private or commercial purpose, subject to the exceptions defined in Section 4.

Contribution, development, and modification of this source code are **strictly reserved** for individuals who **simultaneously** meet both of the following criteria:

- **a)** Being explicitly listed on the repository's official contributor list.
- **b)** Having received a formal invitation or written authorization from the project owners.

---

## 3. Public Access and Visibility

Public access to this GitHub repository is provided solely for purposes of **consultation, transparency, and auditing** by the student community.

No license to reproduce or exploit the contents is implicitly granted by this public visibility.

---

## 4. API Exception

As an exception to the restrictions above, the **application programming interface (API)** of this application is made available for integration and extension purposes.

The specific terms of use and access for this API are governed separately and can be found on the official repository:

📦 [`github.com/hei-tech-dev-team/stdhub-api`](https://github.com/hei-tech-dev-team/stdhub-api)

